            <div style="background-color: #e3e4eb; padding: 1rem;">
                <h4>What does each "Next Step" mean?</h4>
                <hr></hr>
                <p style="margin-top: 2rem;"><strong>Contact Contractor: </strong>The initial email to the main contact for the contractor needs to be completed. In this you will email the contractor letting them know you are interested in beginning the close-out process for this project.</p>
                <p style="margin-top: 2rem;"><strong>Waiting for Contractor Response: </strong>The initial contact email has been sent and you are waiting for a response from the contractor.</p>  
                <p style="margin-top: 2rem;"><strong>Check Contractor Affidavit Format: </strong>The contractor has responded, but you will need to ensure that they have filled out the affidavit correctly.</p>
                <p style="margin-top: 2rem;"><strong>Schedule Final Walkthrough: </strong>The final walkthrough needs to be scheduled with the contractor.</p>
                <p style="margin-top: 2rem;"><strong>Complete Final Walkthrough: </strong>The final walkthrough has been scheduled and you are waiting to complete it on the scheduled time.</p>
                <p style="margin-top: 2rem;"><strong>Upload Walkthrough: </strong>The final walkthrough has been completed and the report needs to be uploaded to your company's files.</p>
                <p style="margin-top: 2rem;"><strong>Perform Testing: </strong>If all testing will need to be scheduled and completed.</p>
                <p style="margin-top: 2rem;"><strong>Upload Testing Results: </strong>All test results and reports need to be uploaded to your company's files.</p>
                <p style="margin-top: 2rem;"><strong>Pending remaining DDS: </strong>You are waiting for the contractor to send all DDSS documentation.</p>
                <p style="margin-top: 2rem;"><strong>Waiting for DDS Internal Review: </strong>All DDSS documents have been sent from the contractor, but your appointed colleague needs to review and approve all of the documentation.</p>
                <p style="margin-top: 2rem;"><strong>Submit DDS to City: </strong>All DDSS documents have been approved and need to be emailed to the City for approval.</p>
                <p style="margin-top: 2rem;"><strong>Pending City Approval: </strong>The DDSS documents have been sent to the city and you are waiting for the City to respond.</p>
                <p style="margin-top: 2rem;"><strong>Upload DDS Approval Letter: </strong>The City has responded and approved your DDSS submission. Upload the approval letter that was sent to your company's files.</p>
                <p style="margin-top: 2rem;"><strong>Sign and Noterized Affidavit: </strong>The project manager will need to sign and noterize the affidavit.</p>
                <p style="margin-top: 2rem;"><strong>Send signed affidavit to City: </strong>The signed affidavit will need to be sent to the City to be recorded.</p>
                <p style="margin-top: 2rem;"><strong>PROJECT COMPLETE: </strong>All items have been completed and this project is offically close-out.</p>
            </div>

            <br></br>

